<svg viewBox="0 0 680 470" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" font-family="system-ui, sans-serif">
<title>Psoriatic epigenetic memory validated model</title>
<desc>Normal skin has active GATA differentiation enhancers; in psoriasis those enhancers are methylated at the basal stage, silencing differentiation; after phototherapy inflammation clears but 72% of the methylation persists as memory, a candidate relapse substrate. Validated: silencing memory replicates p=2.6e-86, scar biomarker cross-cohort AUROC 0.84, permanence predictable AUROC 0.82.</desc>
</svg>
